    <abstract>
      <title>Abstract</title>
      <p>This article deals with a Windows (© Microsoft Inc.) executable, user-friendly
program that tests the hypothesis of Hardy-Weinberg (HW) proportions from
autosomal multiallelic data using different methods that include parametric,
nonparametric and exact bootstrap tests, the latter obtained through computer
simulations. The program can be obtained free of charge directly from the
internet repository <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/Lemes-RenanB/HardyWeinbergTesting">https://github.com/Lemes-RenanB/HardyWeinbergTesting</ext-link>.</p>
    </abstract>
